From the wikipedia article on Werewolves:
> A notable exception to the association of Lycanthropy and the Devil, comes from a rare and lesser known account of an 80-year-old man named Thiess. In 1692, in Jürgensburg, Livonia, Thiess testified under oath that he and other werewolves were the Hounds of God.[48] He claimed they were warriors who went down into hell to do battle with witches and demons. Their efforts ensured that the Devil and his minions did not carry off the grain from local failed crops down to hell. Thiess was steadfast in his assertions, claiming that werewolves in Germany and Russia also did battle with the devil's minions in their own versions of hell, and insisted that when werewolves died, their souls were welcomed into heaven as reward for their service. Thiess was ultimately sentenced to ten lashes for idolatry and superstitious belief.

La Mulana had an interesting take on this kind of thing; 7 other sapient races existed before modern humans did, though all of them resided within the titular ruins.

In order, it went:
>The First Children, who had human torsos but a serpent-like lower body. Mostly destroyed after attempting to claim the Mother's power for an unknown third party
>The Second Children, who were the Giants/Gigas, and sought to return the Mother to space. Destroyed in a massive civil war, with no survivors.
>The Third Children were the Olympians, winged humanoids who created horrific war machines from the remains of the First Children; exiled to Eg-Lana for their hubris.
>The Fourth Children, who had the bodies of fish. Bunch of dumbasses, didn't really do a whole lot. Wiped out as a result.
>The Fifth Children, who were dorfs. Built a helluva lot of nifty tech, some of it being damn near magical and most of it being actually magic. Got to smart for their own good, but created...
>The Sixth Children, who were made in the image of modern humans, and their bodies were made of clay and given life by the Sephirot, a machine that siphoned the Mother's power to create life. Still alive.
>The Seventh Children, who directly predate humanity. Relegated to a small village outside of the main ruins. Might be far, far older than they look.
>And us, the Eighth Children, who were made to be as distant to the Mother as possible for the express purpose of killing her.

Anyhow, most anthros in that game are the result of Chimeratization tech that the Annunaki tried to use to hijack the Mother's power for their own gain. And it works on other humanoids, too. And machines.
